<p>
<seg id="1">Czechs have quickly taken to free roaming, using more data abroad than at home.</seg>
<seg id="2">Czechs consume more of their tariffs abroad than at home.</seg>
<seg id="3">They travel in Austria most often, but in the summer season the consumption of data is dominated by Croatia.</seg>
<seg id="4">While on holiday, they have more time to browse the web, and most of the time they are not able to connect to Wi-Fi under the breach umbrellas.</seg>
<seg id="5">Beach and bathing, smart phone in hand.</seg>
<seg id="6">This is how a typical Czech holiday in Croatia looks now that customers can use services by local operators as part of their home tariffs.</seg>
<seg id="7">O2 recently released statistics painting this picture.</seg>
<seg id="8">Thanks to the new roaming rules, most Czech travellers abroad can access more data as part of their normal rate at home.</seg>
<seg id="9">It's no wonder, then, that in Croatia, where a minimal amount of our countrymen go in winter, consumption of data rose by as much as fifty times this summer.</seg>
<seg id="10">Italy ranked second in the list of consumed data.</seg>
<seg id="11">Czechs use the most minutes calling from Germany, where they go to work a lot during the summer.</seg>
<seg id="12">According to the Association of Czech Travel Agencies, 800,000 Czechs visit Croatia each year, making it our most popular holiday destination.</seg>
<seg id="13">People have swapped their holiday books for sharing their experiences on their mobile phones.</seg>
<seg id="14">The record was 7 July.</seg>
<seg id="15">"Tens of millions of photographs were transferred with the data," said Silvia Cieslarová, director of the O2 mobile department.</seg>
<seg id="16">Although Croatia comes first in terms of the volume of data, the highest number of Czech users can be found in neighbouring countries.</seg>
<seg id="17">Austria is in first place, followed by Germany and Slovakia.</seg>
<seg id="18">Croatia is fourth and Italy sixth.</seg>
<seg id="19">We go to Austria for hiking and active holidays, meaning we do not have much time to browse the internet.</seg>
<seg id="20">"Most Czechs head through Austria towards the Adriatic," Cieslarová explained.</seg>
<seg id="21">While the operator recorded a year-on-year growth in roaming charges, the number of phone calls remains much lower.</seg>
<seg id="22">The number of minutes used while roaming double in relation to the previous year.</seg>
<seg id="23">Germany dominates with a huge lead over other countries.</seg>
<seg id="24">"Calls while roaming are more likely to be made by business customers on work trips," Cieslarová added.</seg>
</p>
</doc>
