<p>
<seg id="1">Chicken skin king Láďa Hruška is facing the challenge of his life.</seg>
<seg id="2">He wants a lesson from Pohlreich!</seg>
<seg id="3">This multifaceted picture began to emerge thanks to the new show "Zdeňkova akademie" on TV Prima.</seg>
<seg id="4">Hruška immediately grabbed his chance.</seg>
<seg id="5">"Dear Zdeněk, I would like to apply to your cooking academy, because, hand on heart, I think I can learn a lot from you," he said in a video shared on social media.</seg>
<seg id="6">And since the two of them have been quarrelling for several years, Láďa did not miss the opportunity to irritate afforded to him.</seg>
<seg id="7">"In return, I can teach you the Znojmo way of cooking chicken meat, American cucumbers or invite you to go canoeing and show you why fried cheese is a favourite," provoked Hruška.</seg>
<seg id="8">He's taking his participation in Pohlreich's new show very seriously.</seg>
<seg id="9">It is time to move up a level and learn from the master.</seg>
<seg id="10">"It's question of being a chef," he told Blesk.</seg>
<seg id="11">Pohlreich did not comment because he was filming new episodes of his next show "Ano, šéfe!"</seg>
