<seg id="1">Young woman gets stuck in a swamp at Lake Mácha and the police wade in after her.</seg>
<seg id="2">The girl set off to the beach at around 2 o'clock in the morning on Sunday.</seg>
<seg id="3">Instead of swimming, she got trapped in the wetlands.</seg>
<seg id="4">When she decided to call the police with her mobile phone, she had just 12 percent of battery left.</seg>
<seg id="5">"Because of that, the police soon lost contact with her," shared police spokesperson Ivana Baláková.</seg>
<seg id="6">Several police patrols went to the site she described, but finding the young woman was no easy task.</seg>
<seg id="7">"Some of the police officers had to wade through reed marshes for hundreds of metres before they felt the ground under their feet again," stated Baláková.</seg>
<seg id="8">And yet she was still missing.</seg>
<seg id="9">The police officers orientated themselves according to the direction of her call for help.</seg>
<seg id="10">"In order not to miss this connection at least, they agreed with her that they would count out loud," the spokesman said.</seg>
<seg id="11">Police found the woman at 4:15 in the swamps of Borny.</seg>
<seg id="12">She was at the end of both her physical and mental strength, and showed signs of hypothermia.</seg>
